{% extends "base.html.twig" %}

{% block title %}Card Game{% endblock %}

{% block body %}
<article class="art-row">
<div class="div-col-1">
    <h2>Card links</h2>
    <ul class="about-links">
    <li><a href="{{ path('session_content') }}">Session</a></li>
    <li><a href="{{ path('session_delete') }}">Session Delete</a></li>
    <li><a href="{{ path('card_deck') }}">Show the entire deck (sorted)</a></li>
    <li><a href="{{ path('card_deck_shuffle') }}">Show the shuffled deck</a></li>
    <li><a href="{{ path('card_deck_draw') }}">Draw a card</a></li>
    <li><a href="{{ path('card_deck_draw_num',{numCards: 0}) }}">Draw X amount of cards</a></li>
    </ul>
</div>
<div class="div-col-2">
<h1>Card game</h1>

{{ include('flash.html.twig') }}

{# read and display all flash messages #}
{% for label, messages in app.flashes %}
    {% for message in messages %}
        <div class="flash-{{ label }}">
            {{ message }}
        </div>
    {% endfor %}
{% endfor %}

<form class="cardform" method="post" action="">
    <input type="submit" name="do_it" value="Create a deck of cards">
</form>

<p> I've created four different classes: DeckOfCards, CardHand, Card and CardGraphic. Card is the base or parent class for all card classes and thus CardGraphic inherits from Card. 
CardGraphic adds the ability to display its values in a graphical way. CardHand is a class object that can hold an array of Card objects, the same goes for DeckOfCards only that it 
holds up to 52 of the card objects and it has more methods to manipulate them. From sorting, shuffleing to controlling the very existance of the cards. Card objects cannot live outside of 
the CardHand or DeckOfCards thus making up a composition in terms of relationship.</p>
<img class="" src="{{ asset('img/cardUML.png') }}" alt="UML picture">

</div>
</article>
{% endblock %}